===Etymology 1===
Fusion of {{inh|en|enm|redden||to deliver from, rid, clear}} (from {{inh|en|ang|hreddan||to deliver, rescue, free from, take away}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hradjaną||to save, deliver}}) and {{inh|en|enm|ridden||to clear away, remove obstructions}} (from {{inh|en|ang|gehryddan|ġeryddan|to clear land}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*riudijaną||to clear}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*reudh-||to clear land}}. Akin to {{cog|ofs|hredda||to save}}, {{cog|nl|redden||to save, deliver}},{{cog|de|retten||to save, deliver}}, {{m|de|roden||to clear}} and {{m|de|reuten||to clear}}, {{cog|non|ryðja||to clear, empty}}, {{cog|non|hróðja|hrōðja|to clear, strip}}. More at {{m|en|redd}}.

